CAPE TOWN - Triple murder accused Henri van Breda is contradicting himself. That’s according to the prosecution, who claims he left out key details about what transpired after his family was attacked when speaking to his neurologist. Van Breda is accused of axing to death his father, mother, and brother in January 2015. WATCH: Henri van Breda cross-examination continues But state prosecutor Susan Galloway says van Breda gave the doctor sketchy details during consultation. Galloway questions which version given by van Breda should be trusted by the court. The trial continues.  eNCA